	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well....my file splitter just says this for further record:
<br />
<br />Mirroring:Vert.
<br />8K SRAM:Yes.
<br />Mapper 4, MMC3.
<br />Program banks: 16. 16KB each.
<br />But then, CHR-ROM banks: 20. 8KB each. [Why 160K of ROM and not 256?]
<br />
<br />Strange. Why would the SRAM need to be ANY different at all? Very weird. Above my technical knowledge.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


