	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">3gengames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What feature on the NES can access the RAM that fast?</div>
<br />The PPU.
<br />
<br />A half-cycle time of 150 ns sounds like 3.3 MHz, which is just a tad over the PPU's fetch rate (half dot clock). Perhaps it's been hacked to use CHR RAM in order to get around the IRQ counter's limitation.
<br />
<br />Frankly, I think all this could be solved if someone on this board were to just <em>buy</em> one. Yeah, I know, people don't want to patronize alleged scammers, but sometimes there's no better way to catch them.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
